# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 14: chemical short-range order in a high-entropy alloy
#
# Render the equilibrated random CoCrFeNi solid solution (the state saved to
# random.dump by sro.lmp after the 700 K thermalization).  The crystal is
# rebuilt with the same type/subset seeds as in sro.lmp, which reproduces the
# same random chemical decoration, and the thermalized positions and box are
# then overlaid with read_dump.  Element colors (used in all figures of this
# tutorial):  Co = yellow (goldenrod), Cr = red (firebrick),
# Fe = blue (steelblue), Ni = green (seagreen).
# No forces are needed to render images, so pair_style zero is used.

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

lattice fcc 3.56
region box block 0 8 0 8 0 8
create_box 4 box
create_atoms 1 box
# same seeds as sro.lmp -> identical random element assignment
set group all type/subset 2 512 12345
set type 1   type/subset 3 512 23456
set type 1   type/subset 4 512 34567
mass 1 58.933   # Co
mass 2 51.996   # Cr
mass 3 55.845   # Fe
mass 4 58.693   # Ni
pair_style zero 3.0
pair_coeff * *

# overlay the thermalized positions and box from the sro.lmp run
read_dump random.dump 2000 x y z box yes

write_dump all image alloy-geometry.png type type size 1024 1024 &
     zoom 1.2 view 60 30 box yes 0.02 shiny 0.2 ssao yes 4539 0.6 &
     modify backcolor white acolor 1 goldenrod acolor 2 firebrick &
     acolor 3 steelblue acolor 4 seagreen adiam 1 3.0 adiam 2 3.0 &
     adiam 3 3.0 adiam 4 2.5 boxcolor midnightblue element Co Cr Fe Ni
